PROJECT DESCRIPTION:

ActiveCanvasJS is an attempt to replicate the product demoed by Bret Victor in his talk "Inventing on Principle" (http://vimeo.com/36579366, 3:33-16:45)

The first targeted features will be those of the static image manipulation (3:33-9:36), as they are far simpler to implement.

Next will come the animated, state-based features (10:42-16:45).

==================================================================================================================================================================
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
==================================================================================================================================================================

FEATURES:

Name                                   | Static(S)/Animated(A)   |  Status       |  Comments
==============================================================================================================================================================
Live update the canvas                 |           S             |    Completed  | This is a very naive implementation that redraws the entire canvas each time 
                                       |                         |               | a modification is made. A more intelligent system, and the one necessary for 
                                       |                         |               | the state-based animated version, will modify variable values in memory and
                                       |                         |               | update only the affected canvas items.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scroll bar to modify numbers           |           S             |     Partial   | Currently integer numbers will scroll up and down by 100. Brett Victor's
                                       |                         |               | number bar extends when the limit is passed. This is partially implemented 
                                       |                         |               | and buggy in the file "slider_beta.js", but not fully working just yet.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Color picker for hex/rgb values        |           S             | Unimplemented | Working on it. Considering a few different color picking plugins.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Auto-complete variables and methods    |           S             | Unimplemented |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Affected code/canvas item highlighting |           S             | Unimplemented | 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Code pausing                           |           A             | Unimplemented | 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Time slider with input recording       |           A             | Unimplemented | 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Motion trail recording and display     |           A             | Unimplemented | 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Drawing new items with auto-code       |           A             |    Extra      | 
insertion                              |                         |               | 
